BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 186.96 740 Td (10 COMMON COGNITIVE DISTORTIONS) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 72 730 m 540 730 l S Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 705 Td (1. All-or-Nothing Thinking) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 690 Td (Seeing things in black-and-white. Example: 'If I'm not perfect, I'm a failure.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 662 Td (2. Catastrophizing) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 647 Td (Expecting the worst outcome. Example: 'This headache must be a brain tumor.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 619 Td (3. Mind Reading) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 604 Td (Assuming you know what others think. Example: 'They think I'm stupid.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 576 Td (4. Fortune Telling) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 561 Td (Predicting negative outcomes. Example: 'I'll definitely fail the interview.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 533 Td (5. Emotional Reasoning) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 518 Td (Feelings = facts. Example: 'I feel anxious, so something bad will happen.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 490 Td (6. Should Statements) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 475 Td (Rigid rules. Example: 'I should never make mistakes.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 447 Td (7. Labeling) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 432 Td (Defining self by one event. Example: 'I'm a loser' after one setback.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 404 Td (8. Magnification/Minimization) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 90 389 Td (Blowing up negatives, shrinking positives.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 72 361 Td (9. Overgeneralization) Tj ET
